{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_013gZhcwrGVM6JqmT4tLBgvK","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `log4j2.properties` shows that ES 8.x logs to `Console` (stdout) with ECSJsonLayout. There's no file appender. So the ES container is writing all logs to stdout, not to files in `/usr/share/elasticsearch/logs/`.\n\nOnly GC logs go to files in that directory.\n\nFor Filebeat to capture ES logs from a sidecar, I have two options:\n1. Add a file appender to ES's log4j2.properties that writes to the shared emptyDir\n2. Configure Filebeat to use the `container` input type with a HostPath volume\n\nThe cleanest option is to add a `log4j2.override.properties` file (or add a custom log4j2.properties) that adds a RollingFile appender in addition to the Console appender. \n\nI can create a ConfigMap with a custom log4j2.properties that keeps the existing console appender but adds file appenders, then mount it in the ES container to write logs to both stdout and the shared emptyDir volume.\n\nHowever, I need to account for the fact that there are three different StatefulSets running different ES versions—8.11.1, 7.17.9, and another 7.17.9—and they might have different log4j2.properties configurations.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1332,"cache_read_input_tokens":71730,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1332},"output_tokens":33,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e46c215e-a358-4899-91cd-9184d094f1e6","uuid":"dad4b14f-82ed-4190-8151-a695fe37fad8","request_id":"req_011Cc8X7FVY5zxjPLUuB2wRE"}
