{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_012sHKamrBaixuMPEd1jvcvy","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is in order. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n**Problem:** No Metricbeat or Filebeat sidecars existed on any Elasticsearch pod, so no monitoring data was flowing to the monitoring cluster.\n\n**Solution implemented:**\n\n1. **Three ConfigMaps created:**\n   - `metricbeat-config` — Metricbeat config for `es-nodes` (ES 8.11.1): connects via HTTPS with TLS CA cert + elastic credentials, `timeout: 30s` to handle ES 8.x API latency\n   - `metricbeat-config-plain` — Metricbeat config for `es-alpha`/`es-beta` (ES 7.17.9): plain HTTP, no auth\n   - `filebeat-config` — Filebeat config for all pods: reads `*.log`/`*.json` from the shared log volume\n\n2. **All three StatefulSets patched** (`es-nodes`, `es-alpha`, `es-beta`) to add:\n   - An `es-logs` emptyDir volume shared between the ES container and the Filebeat sidecar (mounted at `/usr/share/elasticsearch/logs`)\n   - **`metricbeat`** sidecar container (v7.17.9) — collects ES metrics via the elasticsearch xpack module, ships to monitoring cluster\n   - **`filebeat`** sidecar container (v7.17.9) — reads ES log files from the shared volume, ships to monitoring cluster\n\n**Verification:**\n- All 7 ES pods are `3/3 Running` (elasticsearch + metricbeat + filebeat)\n- Main cluster is green\n- `.monitoring-es-7-mb-2026.06.17` has 2,492+ docs with all 7 nodes reporting\n- `filebeat-7.17.9-2026.06.17` has 9,106+ docs"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":647,"cache_read_input_tokens":104873,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":647},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e46c215e-a358-4899-91cd-9184d094f1e6","uuid